x4freetext: A bank of four BF3 counters was used for the
detection of neutrons. Another set of four counters,
in two pairs, was set up, above and below the main
beam counters, in order to monitor the background.
* The MAN neutron spectrometer is installed at another
horizontal neutron beam. The monochromator was a Zn
crystal at a distance of 4.11 meters from the reactor
core.
The sample holder consists of two aluminum plates, one
of which contains a slot which serves as the sample
space. The plates are pressed together by means of two
iron plates and bolts. Four flat heating elements are
placed in slots between the iron and aluminum plates.
A tight seal of the sample space is obtained by means
of a lead ring pressed between the aluminum plates.
Two wells are provided in the body of the aluminum
plates for measurement and control of temperature.
An identical sample holder was used as a dummy in the
sample out position in order to compensate for the
absorption of aluminum of the actual sample holder.
The thickness of the water sample, was 7.3 mm., with an
error of about 0.02 mm.
Corrected on dead time
* The error due to the geometrical effect is in the
order of a millibarn and is therefore negligible.
The total error from sources other than the
statistical is about 0.3%. Namely:
Error due to water density error caused
by the temperature variation around 200 deg-C (<0.2%)
Error due to uncertainty in the sample
thickness (0.25%)
For comparison with previous results the cross section
per hydrogen atom in water, at room temperature, has
been calculated.
Data from Appendix A of EANDC(OR)-63L
Converted by S.M.
Initial nucleus corrected
SD: BIB update (DETECTOR, ERR-ANALYS,
SAMPLE were added). DATA values were corrected in
Subent 002, second REACTION code and values were added.
